    <div  class="pageContent"> Ready to start using theShell? </div>
    <div  class="sectionHeader">Information</div>
    <div  class="pageContent">
      <ul>
        <li>Currently, the latest version of theShell is theShell 1.3</li>
        <li>theShell has only been tested on Arch Linux. Some users have
          reported success with Fedora.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div  class="sectionHeader">Download from the AUR</div>
    <div  class="pageContent">theShell is available on the AUR under the package
      name <a  href="https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/theshell/">theshell</a></div>
    <div  class="sectionHeader">Build from Source</div>
    <div  class="pageContent">Building from source is easy.
      <ol>
        <li>Install required dependencies.<br>
          Dependencies include:
          <ul>
            <li>qmake</li>
            <li>wmctrl</li>
            <li>xbacklight</li>
            <li>alsa-utils (optional, for volume controls)</li>
            <li>pocketsphinx (optional, for theWave)</li>
            <li>festival (optional, for theWave)</li>
            <li>kwin 5+ (default window manager. If you want to use something
              else, theShell will ask you if it can't start KWin.)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Download the sources.<br>
          <code>$ git clone https://github.com/vicr123/theshell<br>
            $ cd theshell</code> </li>
        <li>Build the package. <br>
          <code>$ qmake<br>
            $ make</code></li>
        <li>Copy files to directories<br>
          <code> # cp theshell /usr/bin <br>
            # cp init_theshell /usr/bin <br>
            # cp theshell.desktop /usr/share/xsessions </code> </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
